description:
This MR depends on !602 to be merged first. It propagates warning and error occurring during parsing and building of taclets more reliable and in a format that is understood by the IssueDialog.

This revealed two mistakes in rules for floating points and permutation of sequents where taclets used undeclared rulesets

@mulbrich: I added you just to be sure with the floating point rule. The rule that used a not declared ruleset "executeDoubleAssignment" is in floatAssignment2UpdateRules.key (should that be an own ruleset or something like simplify_prog?)
